## Context
Code organization, analysis, and quality standards

## Requirements
1. Code Organization:
   - Use consistent file structure
   - Follow naming conventions
   - Implement modular design
   - Maintain clean architecture
   - Document dependencies

2. Analysis Standards:
   - Static code analysis
   - Security scanning
   - Performance profiling
   - Type checking
   - Linting enforcement

3. Quality Gates:
   - Test coverage requirements
   - Security compliance
   - Performance thresholds
   - Documentation standards
   - Code review criteria

4. Automation:
   - Automated testing
   - CI/CD integration
   - Code quality checks
   - Documentation generation
   - Dependency updates

5. Monitoring:
   - Performance metrics
   - Error tracking
   - Usage analytics
   - Security alerts
   - Technical debt

## Implementation
1. Set up analysis tools
2. Configure quality gates
3. Implement automation
4. Enable monitoring
5. Track metrics